pullsbody:
Fixes #24


As of January 1 2019, Mozilla requires that all GitHub projects include this [CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md](https://github.com/mozilla/repo-templates/blob/master/templates/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) file in the project root. The file has two parts:

1. Required Text - All text under the headings *Community Participation Guidelines and How to Report*, are required, and should not be altered.
2. Optional Text - The Project Specific Etiquette heading provides a space to speak more specifically about ways people can work effectively and inclusively together. Some examples of those can be found on the [Firefox Debugger](https://github.com/devtools-html/debugger.html/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) project, and [Common Voice](https://github.com/mozilla/voice-web/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md). (The optional part is commented out in the [raw template file](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mozilla/repo-templates/blob/master/templates/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md), and will not be visible until you modify and uncomment that part.)

If you have any questions about this file, or Code of Conduct policies and procedures, please see [Mozilla-GitHub-Standards](https://wiki.mozilla.org/GitHub/Repository_Requirements) or email Mozilla-GitHub-Standards+CoC@mozilla.com.

_(Message COC002)_
pull_repo_desc: Dashboard for the Observatory that gives a quick heads-up view of Mozilla sites
pull_commit_message:
Add Mozilla Code of Conduct file

Fixes #24.

_(Message COC002)_

These include sites that don't resolve, CDNs, APIs, dev/staging sites, most community sites, and static sites for decomissioned projects. I've created a new grouping of "Untracked Sites" which contains all the sites that were found to meet the criteria above.

pull_commit_message:
Move a number of community, dead, or decommissioned sites
In consultation with WebOps, a number of sites that we were tracking should not be tracked against our OKR. I have pushed those sites down to a new Untracked Sites category. They will still be visible on the dashboard but not part of the sites that get tracked and analyzed for the OKR.

pulltitle: Open dashboard links in new tab
pullsbody:
Current logic loads the links in the current tab/frame, and may or may not load them correctly, depending on their CSP configuration.

This opens the links into a new browser tab, ensuring they don't lead to a referrer/opener exploit.
pull_repo_desc: Dashboard for the Observatory that gives a quick heads-up view of Mozilla sites
pull_commit_message:
Open dashboard links in new tab

Current logic loads the links in the current tab/frame, and may or may
not load them correctly, depending on their CSP configuration.

This simply pops them into a new tab.
